    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-11-04T10:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-11-04T10:35:00-05:00" n="249"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <head>249. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Jordan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d249fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66,
                        DEF 12–4 ISR. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_WWD1"
                            >Wolle</persName> on October 29; cleared by George D. Monk of <gloss
                            target="#t_INR1">INR</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_Res1">RES</gloss>, John
                        P. Trevithick of SCI, Beam, <persName corresp="#p_SHM1">Symmes</persName>,
                        and <persName corresp="#p_DRP1">Davies</persName>; and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>. Repeated to Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-11-04T10:35:00-05:00">November 4, 1965, 10:35 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>197. Amman’s 241,<note n="2" xml:id="d249fn2">Telegram 241 from Amman, October
                        25, reported a conversation with Foreign Minister Nuseibeh in which Nuseibeh
                        referred to his meeting with <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> at
                        the <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> General Assembly in New York and
                        expressed the hope that in due course <persName>Barnes</persName> would have
                        a message for him concerning this. (Ibid., REF 3 <gloss target="#t_UNRWA1"
                            >UNRWA</gloss>) Memoranda of the conversation between <persName
                            corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> and Nuseibeh are ibid., Conference
                        Files: Lot 66 D 347, CF 2548.</note> last paragraph.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> Nuseibeh during October 6 talk
                        with Secretary said <gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> convinced Israel had
                        already attained capability producing nuclear bomb, also predicted Israel’s
                        rocket program had advanced to point <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> by
                        March 1966 would demonstrate capability firing rockets that could carry
                        nuclear warheads. Copies relevant memcons being pouched. Embassy should
                        convey following orally to Nuseibeh:</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> has asked me tell you
                            <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> continues watch very closely
                        possible nuclear weapons capability and acquisition by Near Eastern
                        countries. We are most strongly opposed to idea nuclear proliferation in
                        Near East as elsewhere. We have no evidence that Israel or any other Near
                        Eastern state is in position to develop nuclear weapons in near future or
                        that they have decided develop or otherwise acquire them. <gloss
                            target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> vigilance this matter will continue as will
                        our efforts secure effective worldwide nuclear non-proliferation agreement.
                        Meanwhile Arab Governments particularly <gloss target="#t_UAR1">UAR</gloss>
                        could take very important <pb facs="0545" n="513" xml:id="pg_513"/> step
                        toward elimination danger nuclear spread in Near East by undertaking accept
                            <gloss target="#t_IAEA1">IAEA</gloss> safeguards on existing and future
                        nuclear facilities since this would clearly put pressure on Israel do
                        likewise.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
